{
  "texts": [
    "The advantage of differential privacy is that, if the levels of noise are appropriately controlled, one can retain the statistical properties of a dataset, and therefore still allow AI to learn the required knowledge needed to generate accurate predictions.",
    "Suppose an AI pollster has access to a large database of users.",
    "They wish to query this database to understand the relationship between demographics and voting behaviour.",
    "But if enough demographic attributes are specified in the query, individuals in the database can be identified-i.e., if I know all of their attributes, I know exactly who they are.",
    "Differential privacy allows for the protection of the privacy of an individual, by randomly adding imperfections to the attributes in the dataset, such that they no longer perfectly define any specific individual."
  ]
}